  "name": "Geological Time",
  "mood": "Submerged",
  "engines": [
    "Obrix"
  ],
  "description": "A single Sine source — nothing else. Time is the instrument. Envelope parameters are maximized: attack=4.5 seconds, decay=6.0 seconds, sustain=0.98, release=8.0 seconds — the longest release in this collection. Journey Mode means notes have no end; the 8-second release is purely hypothetical. drift ultra-slow (0.004 Hz) allows the frequency to migrate over minutes of play. Four mods are present but all operate glacially: LFO->Pitch at 0.004 Hz (tuning drift), Env->Volume (the long bloom), Velocity->FilterCutoff (the only variable in this stone garden), Aftertouch->FXMix (going deeper into reverb). This preset measures time in strata, not beats.",
